  "prompt": "How can I do effective brainstorming in public speaking?",
  "response": "Here are some effective brainstorming techniques for public speaking:\n\n1. Mind Mapping\n- Create a visual diagram\n- Start with central topic\n- Branch out with related ideas\n- Helps generate connections\n\n2. Free Writing\n- Write continuously without stopping\n- Don't edit or censor thoughts\n- Set a time limit (10-15 minutes)\n- Capture raw ideas quickly\n\n3. Question Storming\n- Ask multiple questions about your topic\n- Use who, what, when, where, why, how\n- Explore different angles\n- Stimulate creative thinking\n\n4. Group Brainstorming\n- Collaborate with colleagues/peers\n- Use diverse perspectives\n- Encourage wild ideas\n- Build on each other's suggestions\n\n5. SCAMPER Technique\n- Substitute\n- Combine\n- Adapt\n- Modify\n- Put to another use\n- Eliminate\n- Reverse\n\n6. Research and Background Study\n- Read existing materials\n- Gather relevant information\n- Understand current perspectives\n- Identify knowledge gaps\n\n7. Visualization\n- Imagine presenting the speech\n- Think about audience reactions\n- Mentally explore potential scenarios\n\n8. Personal Experience Reflection\n- Draw from personal stories\n- Use real-life examples\n- Connect emotional elements\n\nThese techniques can help generate creative and engaging speech content.",
